      Nd4jCpu.NDArray Nd4jCpu.NDArray.apply(long subArrIdx, org.bytedeco.javacpp.IntPointer dimsToExclude, boolean keepUnitiesInShape)
      evaluates subarray with buffer pointing at this->_buffer and offset defined by given sequential index subArrIdx and dimensions in dimsToExclude subArrIdx - index of current sub-array dimsToExclude - MUST BE SORTED, dimensions to evaluate sub-array along, i.e. when shape is [2,3,4,5] and dimsToExclude={0,2}, then there will be 8 sub-arrays with shape [3,5], and subArrIdx must be in range [0,7] if dimsToExclude is empty then idxRanges containing all zeros (means whole array) will be returned.
      Nd4jCpu.NDArray Nd4jCpu.NDArray.apply(org.bytedeco.javacpp.LongPointer idx) 
      Nd4jCpu.NDArray Nd4jCpu.NDArray.apply(org.bytedeco.javacpp.LongPointer idx, boolean keepUnitiesInShape, boolean isStrided)
      operator returns subarray with buffer pointing at this->_buffer with offset defined by given intervals idx - intervals of indexes which define the subarrays to point on, idx has form {dim0Start,dim0End, dim1Start,dim1End, ....} and length (2 * this->rankOf()) when (dimStart == dimEnd) then whole range will be used for current dimension keepUnitiesInShape - if false then eliminate unities from resulting array shape, for example {1,a,1,b} -> {a,b} isStrided - if true then idx has length (3 * this->rankOf()) and contains additional stride numbers which correspond to stride between dimStart and dimEnd, so structure of idx is like {dim0Start,dim0End,dim0Stride, dim1Start,dim1End,dim1Stride, ....}
